              = \n| leader_title                    = [[Mayor]]\n| leader_name                     = Milan Borovina\n| leader_party                    = [[Serbian Democratic Party (Bosnia and Herzegovina)|SDS]]\n| name                            = \n| image_map1                      = Han Pijesak-naselja.PNG\n}}\n'''Han Pijesak''' ({{lang-sr-cyrl|\u0425\u0430\u043d \u041f\u0438\u0458\u0435\u0441\u0430\u043a}}) is a town and municipality located in [[Republika Srpska]], an entity of [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]]. As of 2013, it has a population of 3,530 inhabitants.\n\n==Settlements==\nAside from the town of Han Pijesak, the municipality consists of the following settlements:\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* [[Babine Gornje]]\n* [[Berkovina]]\n* [[Borovine]] \n* [[Brlo\u017enik]]\n* [[D\u017eimrije]]\n* [[Go\u0111enje]]\n* [[Japaga, Bosnia and Herzegovina|Japaga]]\n* [[Jelovci (Han Pijesak)|Jelovci]]\n* [[Kraljevo Polje]]\n* [[Kram (Han Pijesak)|Kram]]\n* [[Kriva\u010de (Han Pijesak)|Kriva\u010de]]\n* [[Kusa\u010de (Han Pijesak)|Kusa\u010de]]\n* [[Malo Polje (Han Pijesak)|Malo Polje]]\n* [[Mrkalji (Han Pijesak)|Mrkalji]]\n* [[Neri\u0107i]]\n* [[Neva\u010dka]]\n* [[Pjenovac]]\n* [[Plane (Han Pijesak)|Plane]]\n* [[Pod\u017eeplje]]\n* [[Potkozlova\u010da]]\n* [[Ravanjsko]]\n* [[Re\u010dica (Han Pijesak)|Re\u010dica]]\n* [[Rijeke]]\n* [[Rubini\u0107i]]\n* [[Stoborani]] \n* [[\u017deravice, Han Pijesak|\u017deravice]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Demographics==\n\n=== Population ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! colspan=\"6\" |Population of settlements \u2013 Han Pijesak municipality\n|-\n|\n|Setllement\n|1971.\n|1981.\n|1991.\n|2013.\n|-\n|\n|Total\n|7,804\n|6,879\n|6,348\n|3,530\n|-\n|1\n|'''Han Pijesak'''\n|1,487\n|1,695\n|2,117\n|2,018\n|-\n|2\n|Japaga\n|\n|\n|152\n|205\n|-\n|3\n|Kraljevo Polje\n|\n|\n|349\n|393\n|}\n\n===Ethnic composition===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! colspan=\"8\" |Ethnic comosition \u2013 Han Pijesak town\n|-\n|\n|2013.\n|1991.\n|1981.\n|1971.\n|-\n|Total\n|2,018